WEBVTT

00:00.589 --> 00:05.288
<i>[ Sam Narrating ] There are moments</i>
<i>when I leap back in time that remind me</i>
<i>of the evening of my senior prom.</i>

00:05.361 --> 00:09.661
<i>Some of the songs are soft and slow,</i>
<i>and there's always a guy</i>
<i>who didn't bring a date...</i>

00:09.732 --> 00:14.669
<i>and wants to dance with your girl</i>--
<i>guys who don't take no for an answer.</i>

00:14.737 --> 00:20.039
<i>Andjust when everything quiets down,</i>
<i>and you find a song that</i>
<i>you want to dance to forever,</i>

00:22.000 --> 00:28.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:38.060 --> 00:40.221
<i>(music) [ Continues ]</i>

00:54.209 --> 00:56.143
Disco.

01:09.925 --> 01:13.292
[ Thinking ]
Oh, I'd rather be dead.
<i>(music) [ Continues ]</i>

01:15.664 --> 01:17.757
[ Patrons Screaming ]

02:43.452 --> 02:45.716
Chad, you all right, guy?

02:45.788 --> 02:49.588
I've been hit.
<i>[ Man On Bullhorn ]</i>
<i>And cut! Cut it! It's good. Print that one.</i>

02:49.658 --> 02:51.649
<i>[ Light Applause ]</i>
<i>[ Bell Ringing ]</i>

02:51.727 --> 02:53.888
Oh-ho-ho, babe! Good job!

02:53.962 --> 02:57.762
Loved it. Okay.
Okay, next shot is, uh, over here.

02:57.833 --> 03:00.893
Come on. Let's go, let's go.
We're an hour behind here. Let's go.

03:00.969 --> 03:04.200
I'm a stuntman.
Almost a dead one.

03:04.273 --> 03:06.366
I told you to check that safety pad.
I did!

03:06.441 --> 03:08.534
Well, then how come it was moved?
I don't know. I double-checked it.

03:08.610 --> 03:10.874
You almost got
your brother's head caved in.

03:10.946 --> 03:14.347
Whoa, whoa.
Wait-Wait a second. I'm okay.
Stop standing up for him.

03:14.416 --> 03:16.714
Somebody must have moved it
while I was workin' the ratchet.

03:16.785 --> 03:18.980
Come on, guys, huh? Out of the way.

03:19.054 --> 03:22.820
<i>I got shots to get, all right?</i>
Not till I find out
who moved my safety pad!

03:22.891 --> 03:26.088
Hey, not my problem, babe.

03:28.831 --> 03:31.766
Someone gets killed on your set,
it will be. Let's go, guys.

03:31.834 --> 03:35.201
<i>Oh, whoa, whoa.</i>
<i>What's your problem?</i>
<i>You.</i>

03:35.270 --> 03:39.764
You're more concerned about your schedule
than whether somebody gets hurt.
Hey, hey, where you goin'?

03:39.842 --> 03:42.811
- <i>Off this picture.</i>
- Oh, no. You can't quit on me.

03:42.878 --> 03:45.642
Watch me.
Hey, hey, hey.
I already paid you for Friday's stunt.

03:45.714 --> 03:47.944
So I'll pay you back.
All right.
What about you two guys?

03:48.016 --> 03:51.247
- What?
- <i>That's right. You quit, not them.</i>
<i>How about it guys?</i>

03:51.320 --> 03:56.223
You want to work in the disco?
Look, pal, I'm the stunt coordinator here,
and these are my boys.

03:56.291 --> 04:00.227
I don't work, they don't work.
Well, why don't you
let them decide?

04:00.295 --> 04:03.093
Hack.
[ Scoffs ]
Yeah, right. How about it, you guys?

04:05.701 --> 04:08.226
Uh, no, thanks.

04:11.406 --> 04:17.106
How about you, babe?
I mean, uh, this fire thing was
your first big stunt, wasn't it?

04:23.719 --> 04:25.778
No.

04:25.854 --> 04:27.879
Okay.

04:27.956 --> 04:31.119
Okay, okay, what's everybody gawkin' at, huh?
Stop gawkin'!

04:31.193 --> 04:33.991
<i>Line up. Okay, roll playback.</i>
I double-checked it, Chad.
I swear.

04:34.062 --> 04:36.155
<i>[ Clapboard Claps ]</i>
<i>(music) [ Disco ]</i>

04:36.231 --> 04:39.496
Uh,just forget it, okay?
<i>And... action.</i>
Dad won't let me.

04:39.568 --> 04:43.766
Rick's been laying into us for three weeks.
I don't know why Dad had to quit now.

04:43.839 --> 04:47.605
It's two days before my big stunt.
I could have got my union card.

04:47.676 --> 04:51.908
Maybe you could talk to him about it.
Make him change his mind.

04:51.980 --> 04:54.778
Uh, to Dad?

04:54.850 --> 04:57.375
Yeah, get my stunt back for me.

04:57.452 --> 04:59.647
Well, yeah, okay.
I'll-- I'll try.

04:59.721 --> 05:04.351
Are you for real? You're crazy.
I like that in a guy.

05:04.426 --> 05:08.260
Really?
He's done stunts
you wouldn't even dream of.

05:08.330 --> 05:12.232
I don't know.
I've got a pretty vivid imagination.

05:12.301 --> 05:15.031
Traci Duvore, Aquarius.

05:15.103 --> 05:19.631
Boogie Town Records.
We're handling all of the music
on this movie.

05:19.708 --> 05:22.700
You're Chad Stone. Leo, right?

05:23.779 --> 05:25.770
I guess-- I guess so.

05:25.847 --> 05:31.285
[ Laughs ]
I knew it! Oh, you've got ''king of the beasts''
written all over you.

05:31.353 --> 05:34.151
[ Laughs, Mutters ]
Thank you.

05:34.222 --> 05:38.488
Ever, uh, break anything... vital?

05:38.560 --> 05:41.120
<i>Are you kiddin'? He's</i>--
<i>He's broken every bone</i>
<i>in his body.</i>

05:41.196 --> 05:43.187
Every bone?

05:44.900 --> 05:48.461
I gotta get, uh, a...

05:48.537 --> 05:53.031
drink.
Mm-hmm. Come with me, baby.
Come on.

05:53.108 --> 05:55.076
<i>(music) [ Continues ]</i>

06:02.818 --> 06:05.514
Excuse me.

06:05.587 --> 06:08.317
Hi, Chad.

06:08.390 --> 06:12.520
Hi.
Aren't you gonna introduce me
to your new friend?

06:13.895 --> 06:16.090
Oh! Uh, yeah, sure.

06:16.164 --> 06:18.997
This is Traci. Traci, this is--

06:20.769 --> 06:22.930
I'm sorry.
I'm blanking on your name.

06:23.005 --> 06:27.374
Well, you didn't <i>blank</i> on me
in your trailer last night.

06:28.910 --> 06:30.878
Nice to meet ya.

06:35.183 --> 06:37.117
Hey, Chad, nice hit.

06:41.189 --> 06:43.384
[ Laughing ]

06:49.965 --> 06:52.934
<i>[ Laughing ]</i>
<i>Chad?</i>

06:53.001 --> 06:55.367
No matter how hard you look,
it doesn't get any better.

06:59.541 --> 07:02.374
- Nice hickey.
- Hickey?

07:03.445 --> 07:08.576
-<i>[ Rick ] All right. Well</i>-- <i>Huh! I guess</i>
<i>we'll have to</i>--<i>[ Continues, Indistinct ]</i>
- I got a hickey.

07:08.650 --> 07:11.619
Well, it isn't a monkey bump.

07:11.686 --> 07:16.851
Look, Traci, uh, I'll, um--
I'll talk to you in a little bit.

07:16.925 --> 07:19.894
Where you goin'? Sit down.

07:19.961 --> 07:22.225
What're you doin'?

07:22.297 --> 07:25.789
Giving you my mood ring.
Aah!

07:25.867 --> 07:30.895
[ Thinking ] A mood ring from
the self-obsessed '7 0s, when everyone
was getting in touch with their feelings.

07:30.972 --> 07:33.907
It's for getting in touch
with your feelings.

07:33.975 --> 07:36.967
Jade green means you're ultra-intense.
<i>[ Rick ]</i>
<i>Roll playback.</i>

07:37.045 --> 07:40.446
Blue means you're feeling ecstasy.

07:40.515 --> 07:44.349
And reddish brown means
you need to chug some sangria. Hm!

07:44.419 --> 07:47.217
Oh, it's turned black!

07:47.289 --> 07:51.589
That means you're tense,
disoriented, harassed.

07:51.660 --> 07:54.185
[ Thinking ]
Maybe these things work after all.

07:54.262 --> 07:56.492
Call me, and I'll turn it blue.

07:56.565 --> 07:58.556
Hm!

08:09.578 --> 08:11.944
<i>(music) [ Disco ]</i>

08:15.450 --> 08:17.441
Al.

08:23.125 --> 08:25.685
Al, would you--

08:26.695 --> 08:29.892
Would you cut that out?
Would you get over here, please?

08:41.443 --> 08:43.604
He's a real killer, huh?

08:44.746 --> 08:48.910
His clothes are the killer,
and all those gold chains have to go.

08:48.984 --> 08:51.418
[ Chuckles ]
That's my brother.

08:51.486 --> 08:53.511
I guess bad taste isn't genetic.

08:57.259 --> 09:00.092
<i>Does he usually talk to himself?.</i>

09:00.162 --> 09:02.630
Aw, he's just goofin'.

09:02.697 --> 09:05.097
Every girl I've ever met
goes crazy for him.

09:05.167 --> 09:07.158
I'm not every girl.

09:07.235 --> 09:09.226
Really?

09:11.173 --> 09:14.199
What kind of guys do you like?

09:14.276 --> 09:16.267
More natural.

09:16.344 --> 09:20.940
You know,jeans, cowboy boots,

09:21.016 --> 09:24.747
a blue denim shirt with,
uh, pearl buttons.

09:26.788 --> 09:28.915
Really?

09:30.492 --> 09:33.791
<i>[ Rick ]</i>
<i>That's it. All right. Yeah.</i>
<i>Please, cover the floor.</i>

09:33.862 --> 09:36.729
<i>[ Sam ]</i>
<i>Al, this is worse than anything imaginable.</i>

09:36.798 --> 09:42.464
What're you talkin' about, Sam?
You're on the set of a low-budget
disaster movie, <i>Disco Inferno,</i>

09:42.537 --> 09:46.200
with lights, camera,
plenty of action.

09:46.274 --> 09:50.643
You know, I think I saw
this movie once on cable.
We're talkin' two thumbs down.

09:50.712 --> 09:55.615
I'm back in the '7 0s.
Yeah. That was one of
the happiest times in my life.

09:55.684 --> 09:59.518
You had disco, swinging singles,
hot tubs, EST,

09:59.588 --> 10:03.957
uh, mantras, Farrah Fawcett,
eh, edible underwear--

10:04.025 --> 10:08.792
The ''Me Decade,'' where everybody
had the morality of two dogs in a park.

10:09.798 --> 10:13.199
What're you doin'?
What's the matter'?
Ah, my mood ring is stuck.

10:13.268 --> 10:17.261
Oh, gee. Looks like you're
in a bad mood, Sam.

10:18.273 --> 10:21.504
Where am I?
Uh, you're in, uh,

10:21.576 --> 10:23.635
Burbank, California,

10:23.712 --> 10:25.976
April 1 , 1 97 6.

10:26.047 --> 10:29.847
What, are you tellin' me
I'm the butt of some
cosmic April Fool's joke?

10:29.918 --> 10:32.443
<i>What does Ziggy say</i>
<i>I'm here to figure out?</i>

10:33.622 --> 10:35.852
Al?

10:35.924 --> 10:37.858
Al!

10:37.926 --> 10:42.363
Oh, uh-- Oh, Ziggy,
he crashed on us the other night.

10:42.430 --> 10:45.399
Ever since,
he's been doin' screwball things,

10:45.467 --> 10:48.436
like he put extra zeros
on everybody's paycheck.

10:48.503 --> 10:52.667
So half the staff
rushed out on vacation.

10:52.741 --> 10:57.007
Why didn't you go?
I can't go.
I gotta be on standby for you.

10:57.078 --> 11:01.014
Besides, this is like a vacation for me.
I always wanted to be in the movies.

11:01.082 --> 11:05.781
[ Chuckles ]
Great. That's great. You're starstruck.
Al, would you just find out what I'm here to do?

11:05.854 --> 11:08.823
Well, before Ziggy crashed,
he did come up with one thing.

11:10.558 --> 11:13.049
In the next two days, uh,

11:13.128 --> 11:16.427
Chris is gonna die.

11:18.633 --> 11:20.066
Chris?

11:21.636 --> 11:25.128
<i>Yeah, Chris.</i>
<i>He's your little brother.</i>

11:25.206 --> 11:28.266
He dies? How?
I don't know.

11:28.343 --> 11:31.870
<i>[ Rick ] Cut it. Cut it, please. Cut it.</i>
Well, when?
I don't know.

11:31.946 --> 11:33.937
Where?
I don't know.

11:34.015 --> 11:36.779
Will you find out?
I don't know anything
until Ziggy gets fixed.

11:36.851 --> 11:40.981
In the meantime,
you just gotta play big brother,
uh, for a couple of days.

11:41.056 --> 11:46.221
Make sure Chris doesn't do
any stunts or race any fast cars, or,

11:46.294 --> 11:48.455
you know, that he doesn't--

11:49.964 --> 11:51.955
What?

11:53.168 --> 11:56.262
Al, I-- I have a big brother.

11:56.338 --> 12:00.798
Oh, hmm. I was wondering when
you were gonna remember that.

12:00.875 --> 12:03.810
Tom. His name is Tom.

12:03.878 --> 12:06.506
How could I forget
that I have a brother?

12:06.581 --> 12:09.778
The leap Swiss-cheesed
your memory.

12:12.053 --> 12:14.783
I don't remember
anything about him.
Where is he? What's he doin'?

12:14.856 --> 12:17.256
Sam, you know the rules.

12:17.325 --> 12:21.921
I can't tell you any of that.
I don't remember anything.
Come on, Al. Help me.

12:21.996 --> 12:26.865
Sam,just worry about
the little brother down there...
who's gonna die...

12:26.935 --> 12:29.563
in two days.

12:37.278 --> 12:39.872
Toby? We're ready for you.
<i>[ Bell Ringing ]</i>

12:41.383 --> 12:44.216
Toby? We're--

12:47.222 --> 12:49.213
Uh, we're-we're ready.

12:56.698 --> 12:59.792
Hey, Chad.
You're lookin' dy-no-mite.

13:11.980 --> 13:14.642
I ain't gonna let that hack
put us all in jeopardy.

13:15.650 --> 13:18.983
Hey, you gotta understand
this ain't my fault.

13:19.053 --> 13:22.250
We could've finished the show.
One more day wouldn't have
made a difference.

13:22.323 --> 13:25.520
You want to work for me, do what I say.
Otherwise, go to work for someone else.
Got it?

13:25.593 --> 13:28.289
<i>[ Slams Door ]</i>
Got it.
Good.

13:28.363 --> 13:30.695
<i>And ease up on the door.</i>
He's tryin' really hard.

13:30.765 --> 13:34.531
Well, that ain't good enough.
One false move in this business
you're dead, and you know that.

13:34.602 --> 13:37.799
<i>But he won't listen.</i>
Maybe if you wouldn't yell.

13:37.872 --> 13:40.500
What do you want me to do,
baby him like his mother did?

13:40.575 --> 13:44.773
- Well, I'm-I'm not sayin' that--
- What are you sayin'?

13:44.846 --> 13:47.610
You know,just ease up on him a little.

13:52.287 --> 13:57.156
Hey, kiddo, gonna wear
that frown all day?
Come on. Come on.

13:57.225 --> 13:59.625
Come on! Come on. Get set.

13:59.694 --> 14:03.994
Gonna beat yourself. Oh-ho!
Gotcha! Come here, boy.

14:04.065 --> 14:08.195
<i>Look, Chris, the director</i>
<i>in there is dangerous.</i>
<i>He takes too many chances.</i>

14:08.269 --> 14:11.295
You gotta trust me on this.
You'll get your shot soon enough.
I promise.

14:11.372 --> 14:13.863
Yeah? When?

14:14.876 --> 14:19.643
<i>How about it, Chad? We got that stunt</i>
<i>comin'up on</i> Earthquake <i>tomorrow.</i>
<i>You think the boy's ready?</i>

14:19.714 --> 14:23.582
- Well--
- Come on, Chad. I can do it.

14:23.651 --> 14:28.020
- Uh--
- It's your stunt. It's your call.

14:31.826 --> 14:34.090
No.

14:34.162 --> 14:37.256
Chad, you know I'm ready.
It's just a little fall.
<i>Not this time.</i>

14:37.332 --> 14:41.325
- A fall?
- Yeah, it's a piece of cake.

14:41.402 --> 14:44.860
Look, I can't give it to you.
I'm sorry. Uh, next time.

14:44.939 --> 14:46.930
That's it.

14:50.445 --> 14:53.175
It's not that tough a gag, Chad.

14:55.850 --> 14:59.479
5:30 call tomorrow, boys.
Don't be late.

14:59.554 --> 15:01.545
And I could've got my union card
with that stunt.

15:01.623 --> 15:05.252
You'll get it next week.
I've been hearin' that
for nine months.

15:06.928 --> 15:10.887
[ Chuckles ]
Look at these old eight-track tapes.

15:10.965 --> 15:13.195
You just bought those.
<i>[ Engine Revs ]</i>

15:13.268 --> 15:16.465
Yeah, well, they get old pretty fast.

15:17.739 --> 15:23.439
Barry White, the Village People,
Donna Summer, Neil Sedaka,
<i>Kung Fu Fighting.</i>

15:23.511 --> 15:26.537
Wow. Hey, wait a minute!
I'm supposed to drive!

15:27.549 --> 15:31.713
<i>[ Thinking ]</i>
<i>Chris raced back to the marina, with me</i>
<i>telling him to slow down the whole way.</i>

15:31.786 --> 15:35.882
He hardly said a thing.
Can't say I blame him though.

15:35.957 --> 15:40.758
I remember how mad I'd get whenever
I thought Tom was bossing me around.
[ Sighs ]

15:40.828 --> 15:44.958
I see now it just comes
with the job of being a big brother.

15:58.446 --> 16:01.108
Tom played basketball,
high school varsity.

16:01.182 --> 16:05.209
He was All-American,
Indiana State Championships--

16:06.220 --> 16:09.781
It was 1 965-- uh, no, '64--

16:09.857 --> 16:12.052
and...

16:12.126 --> 16:14.117
what happened?

16:15.129 --> 16:17.120
I want to remember,

16:17.198 --> 16:19.826
but... I'm afraid.

16:19.901 --> 16:23.098
Of what?
<i>(music) [ Electric Guitar, Country ]</i>

16:58.539 --> 17:02.737
There's a thing called knocking.
You might want to try it sometime.

17:04.412 --> 17:06.403
[ Knocking ]

17:08.116 --> 17:10.550
You're good.

17:10.617 --> 17:12.643
Too bad you can't
make a living at it.

17:12.720 --> 17:14.711
Why not?

17:14.789 --> 17:17.723
I can't play that disco garbage.
<i>[ Pencil Scratching ]</i>

17:18.925 --> 17:21.486
Disco's not gonna last forever.

17:22.730 --> 17:25.722
I got a feeling it's probably
gonna die in a couple of years.

17:26.901 --> 17:29.461
How do you know?
Just a feeling.

17:29.537 --> 17:31.767
Maybe in a couple years
those disco maniacs...

17:31.839 --> 17:35.605
will become urban cowboys.

17:38.980 --> 17:41.278
How come you didn't
give me my shot?

17:42.283 --> 17:45.150
I got my reasons.
You know, there's still time.

17:45.219 --> 17:47.949
You can just call Dad and tell him
I'm the one who's gonna do it.
Chris. Chris.

17:48.022 --> 17:50.752
I'm doing the stunt.
[ Sighs ]

17:51.759 --> 17:55.889
You know, you're some big brother.
You're always there when I need ya.

17:56.898 --> 17:59.423
You know, it's funny. Uh,

17:59.500 --> 18:01.866
big brothers sometimes
do things that...

18:01.936 --> 18:06.236
little brothers can't quite understand.
Like what?

18:06.307 --> 18:08.400
I knew these two brothers.

18:09.410 --> 18:11.571
The older one was a terrific athlete--

18:11.646 --> 18:13.580
basketball, track, football, the works.

18:13.648 --> 18:18.051
The younger brother was good,
too, but his real gift was in physics.

18:18.119 --> 18:22.351
But the kid fought it.
You know, he wanted to be
just like his big brother.

18:22.423 --> 18:24.983
But the brother knew.

18:25.059 --> 18:28.392
He pushed that kid
to follow his talents,

18:29.397 --> 18:31.661
convinced him to go to MIT.

18:32.667 --> 18:35.602
Kid won a Nobel Prize.

18:36.637 --> 18:38.832
Yeah.

18:38.906 --> 18:41.238
Well, I'm not winnin' any Grammys.

18:42.243 --> 18:44.609
You don't know unless you try.

18:44.679 --> 18:47.273
<i>[ Doorbell Rings ]</i>

18:52.153 --> 18:55.054
She showed up!
I-I can't believe it!

18:55.123 --> 18:57.421
Shannon, the girl I met
on the set today!

18:57.492 --> 19:00.222
Uh, listen, Chad,

19:00.294 --> 19:02.285
do me a favor, will ya?

19:02.363 --> 19:04.524
Just don't hit on her.
Why would I hit on her?

19:04.599 --> 19:07.329
Because you hit on everybody.
Promise me.

19:07.401 --> 19:10.529
Yeah, okay, I promise.
I won't hit on her.
[ Sighs ]

19:14.242 --> 19:16.836
Cross my heart.

19:16.911 --> 19:18.902
What heart?

19:20.748 --> 19:25.344
[ Bell Dings ]
Sandwich. All right.
That's acceptable. Okay.

19:25.419 --> 19:31.153
Twelve people said sandwich.
All right, Connie:
something that people like to bite.

19:31.225 --> 19:33.216
Mmm, the big one.

19:33.294 --> 19:36.286
[ Audience Laughing ]
Bite the big one. All right.

19:36.364 --> 19:38.628
- <i>Does our audience bite the big one?</i>
-<i>[ Beldar Conehead ] Proceed.</i>

19:38.699 --> 19:40.826
[ Buzzer Buzzes ]
Something you eat with eggs.

19:40.902 --> 19:42.893
Fiberglass.
[ Buzzer Buzzes ]

19:42.970 --> 19:46.133
[ Audience Laughing ]
Okay, Beldar. Very interesting.

19:46.207 --> 19:49.802
You're on quite a roll there, fella--
no points, no money.
Don't feel bad about it though.

19:49.877 --> 19:53.040
We'll be back tomorrow,
and you'll have another chance
at the fast money.

19:53.114 --> 19:57.847
Until then, everybody, remember old people
are our greatest natural resource.
[ Beldar Imitates Buzzer]

19:57.919 --> 20:00.649
So check in on one today
and push 'em around the block.
[ Imitates Buzzer]

20:00.721 --> 20:03.349
So long, everybody.
