<i>[ Sam Whooping ]</i>
<i>[ Shannon ]</i>
<i>All right, Chris!</i>

31:46.593 --> 31:49.221
<i>[ Crowd Cheering ]</i>

31:52.499 --> 31:56.902
<i>[ Man On P.A.]</i>
<i>Ow! That was Chris Stone,</i>
<i>a young man who's gonna go far!</i>

31:58.005 --> 32:00.473
All right! Excellent.

32:02.376 --> 32:07.075
[ Clears Throat ]

32:07.147 --> 32:09.513
<i>(music) [ Traditional Country ]</i>

32:10.617 --> 32:13.415
Well, what'd you think?

32:18.525 --> 32:20.686
I think you're wastin' your time.

32:21.929 --> 32:24.523
Oh, come on, Dad.
He was good tonight.
Everybody loved him.

32:24.598 --> 32:29.262
You know, he got more applause tonight
than I did on my stunt this morning.
Chad, forget it. He doesn't care, okay?

32:29.336 --> 32:31.702
Oh, come on.
Did I hurt your feelings, kid?

32:31.772 --> 32:35.936
Come on. Put up your dukes.
Come on, come on. Don't you
wanna box with your old man?

32:36.009 --> 32:38.603
Take it easy, take it easy.
Don't worry.Just playin' around.
Afraid I'll whup ya?

32:38.679 --> 32:42.137
- If I'd have raised you
instead of your mom, you'd be--
-<i>[ Shannon ] Chris!</i>

32:42.215 --> 32:44.843
<i>[ Bottle Crashes ]</i>

32:45.919 --> 32:48.387
Ohh.

32:48.455 --> 32:51.117
The boy do know how to punch,
doesn't he?

32:51.191 --> 32:53.716
Lucky for him
that you was holdin' me.

32:53.794 --> 32:56.627
[ Chuckles ]
Lucky for you
he only threw one.

33:03.604 --> 33:06.129
[ Line Ringing ]
[ Rick ]
Yeah, hello?

33:06.206 --> 33:08.674
Yeah, Rick, it's Chris Stone.

33:08.742 --> 33:11.711
Hey, man, you don't call
the director at home.

33:11.778 --> 33:15.646
Look, I know my dad quit on you,
but you got anybody
for the fire stunt tomorrow?

33:15.716 --> 33:18.446
Huh! Babe,
I don't have a Stone.

33:19.453 --> 33:22.183
You got one now.
[ Line Clicks ]

33:27.728 --> 33:29.719
Chris?

33:35.769 --> 33:37.760
Chris?

33:53.387 --> 33:55.378
<i>[ Al ]</i>
<i>Cute kids.</i>

33:56.523 --> 34:01.426
Al, look,
I gotta get outta here.

34:01.495 --> 34:07.024
There's somethin' about this leap
that's drivin' me crazy. I mean,
I don't even know what it is.

34:07.100 --> 34:10.900
- Chris givin' you a hard time?
- No matter what I tell him,
you know, he won't listen.

34:10.971 --> 34:14.031
Well, sometimes it's tough
bein' a big brother.

34:14.107 --> 34:16.940
Yeah, now I know how Tom felt.

34:17.010 --> 34:20.275
I always thought he was putting me down--
you know, trying to tell me what to do.

34:20.347 --> 34:24.476
But by the time I figured out
he was just lookin' out for me,
it was too late, because he--

34:29.723 --> 34:31.714
Tom's dead, isn't he?

34:35.027 --> 34:37.018
Come on, Al.

34:39.299 --> 34:41.290
Yeah.

34:42.302 --> 34:44.463
He was killed in Vietnam.

34:58.251 --> 35:02.153
That's one part of your memory
I was hoping you wouldn't get back.

35:23.043 --> 35:25.102
<i>[ Dog Barking ]</i>

35:29.149 --> 35:31.140
No date?

35:31.218 --> 35:36.087
What?
Well, you're usually droppin' off
some skirt this early in the morning.

35:37.090 --> 35:39.991
Look, Chris didn't come home last night.
I was hoping he came by here.

35:40.060 --> 35:42.756
What for?
To admire the damage?

35:42.829 --> 35:44.820
I'm worried about him.

35:44.898 --> 35:49.335
Well, if I know my boys,
he's out with that little brunette.
He'll be home in a couple of days.

35:49.402 --> 35:52.860
What makes you so sure
he'll come back?

35:52.939 --> 35:55.533
What the hell else is he gonna do,
be a musician?
Why not?

35:55.609 --> 35:59.670
I thought we went
all through this last night.
No, we didn't settle it. Chris was great.

35:59.746 --> 36:03.182
Sure, he was good.
Well, he needed
to hear that from you.

36:03.250 --> 36:06.048
Look, that don't mean that
I want him to go and ruin his life.
Yeah, but don't you see?

36:06.119 --> 36:09.145
That's exactly what you're doing
by forcing him to become a stuntman.

36:09.222 --> 36:11.213
[ Sighs ]

36:12.526 --> 36:14.926
I don't know.

36:14.995 --> 36:18.829
You know, sometimes I find myself
doing the same thing to Chris
that my daddy did to me.

36:20.600 --> 36:22.932
I can't seem to stop myself.

36:23.937 --> 36:28.601
Your granddaddy was a stuntman
so I became a stuntman, because I
had to prove to him that I could do it.

36:28.675 --> 36:31.303
And I did.

36:31.378 --> 36:36.247
I don't know. I guess--
I guess provin' things
is in the old Stone blood, huh?

36:40.287 --> 36:44.314
Like Chris proving
he has to do that fire stunt.

36:47.661 --> 36:49.891
<i>[ Rick ]</i>
<i>Come on. I don't care.Just wire it</i> --

36:49.963 --> 36:53.865
Rick, here's your coffee.
I don't have time to do
anything like that.

36:53.934 --> 36:57.097
Ugh! Yo, uh, Hoss.

36:57.170 --> 36:59.161
Come here.
Yes, sir?

36:59.239 --> 37:02.640
I tell you three lumps of sugar?
Three. I mean, you get that, right?
Oh, I'm sorry. Yeah.

37:02.709 --> 37:05.769
I mean, you understand that?
Good. Then do it. Okay?
Yeah, I understand.

37:05.846 --> 37:10.146
All right. You got it.
Geez, who do I gotta sleep with to get
a decent cup of coffee around here?

37:10.217 --> 37:13.243
Chris, babe! You made it.

37:13.320 --> 37:17.154
And, uh, you brought us
a cheerleader, huh?
Uh, no. This is Shannon.

37:17.224 --> 37:19.385
Hey, nice to meet you,
sweet-face.

37:19.459 --> 37:23.395
Now, listen, we're gonna be up
for you in about 1 0 minutes, man.
Hit wardrobe. Hang tight. Let's go.

37:23.463 --> 37:26.193
You, come on. Let's go.
All right. Let's-- Everybody, let's go!

37:26.266 --> 37:30.134
Time is money! I have to say it again?
All right. Come on. This is a difficult stunt.

37:30.203 --> 37:32.899
Chris, are you sure
you want to do this?

37:32.973 --> 37:35.271
What do you mean?
I don't know.

37:35.342 --> 37:38.505
I mean, shouldn't your father be here
to check this out or something?

37:38.578 --> 37:40.705
Look, I already
checked it out, okay?

37:40.780 --> 37:42.771
What about your brother?

37:42.849 --> 37:45.477
He told me to do
whatever I wanted to do.

37:45.552 --> 37:47.543
So I am, all right?

37:55.095 --> 37:57.256
Come on. Take me up!

37:57.330 --> 37:59.560
Let's go. Be careful.

37:59.633 --> 38:03.660
Okay. Uh, what's his--
what's his name? Chris!

38:03.737 --> 38:08.174
<i>Chris, look, as you run there'll be</i>
<i>some more squib hits on the wall.</i>

38:08.241 --> 38:12.041
Okay, as you run across
there'll be a flash-pot blows up,

38:12.112 --> 38:15.138
forcing you over to here,
which is where you hit the mini-tramp.

38:15.215 --> 38:17.809
<i>And that's where the big explosion</i>
<i>takes place, okay?</i>

38:17.884 --> 38:20.580
You fly over the ledge;
you crash down on the boxes.

38:20.654 --> 38:23.122
You got it? Huh?

38:23.189 --> 38:26.317
<i>Good. All right. Come on.</i>
<i>Take me down.</i>

38:26.393 --> 38:29.123
<i>Come on. I hate this thing.</i>
<i>Let's go, let's go, people!</i>

38:29.195 --> 38:33.154
We're an hour behind. Come on!
Rick, Rick, shouldn't we,
uh, get a rehearsal first?

38:33.233 --> 38:36.396
Ah, hell with it.
We'll shoot the rehearsal, all right?
<i>[ Man ] We are ready!</i>

38:36.469 --> 38:39.802
Come on! I said, we're gonna
shoot the rehearsal! Let's go!
<i>We're gonna shoot the rehearsal!</i>

38:39.873 --> 38:42.034
Come on.
Can I get off of this thing?
Yeah.

38:43.910 --> 38:46.435
All right. Come on. Positions! Let's go!

38:46.513 --> 38:50.847
- <i>Okay, come on, come on, come on. Stand by</i>
<i>to roll cameras. Ready, special effects.</i>
-<i>[ Man ] Stand by to roll!</i>

38:50.917 --> 38:53.715
- Ready, Chris, babe?
- Yes, sir.

38:53.787 --> 38:56.221
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Background, stand by! Quiet on the set!</i>

38:56.289 --> 38:59.690
- Roll cameras.
-<i>[ Man ] ''A''camera rolling.</i>

39:01.628 --> 39:03.619
[ Tires Screech ]

39:06.933 --> 39:08.901
And... action!

39:09.970 --> 39:12.734
- Hey, Chad!
- [ Explosions ]

39:14.307 --> 39:16.537
<i>[ Crew Screaming ]</i>

39:19.212 --> 39:22.477
What happened?

39:23.984 --> 39:27.545
-<i>[ Sam ] Chris!</i>
- [ Man ] Go! Get out, get out! Move it!

39:27.620 --> 39:29.087
Come on!
Aah!

39:29.155 --> 39:32.147
Chris! Chris!

39:32.225 --> 39:35.991
Chris! Chris is in there!
Dad, get back!

39:36.062 --> 39:38.053
I gotta get him out!
I know.

39:38.131 --> 39:40.361
Let go of me!
Dad, I'll find him.

39:40.433 --> 39:44.392
Come on, guys. Take him out.
Don't! Let me go!

39:44.471 --> 39:46.701
<i>Let me go!</i>

39:47.874 --> 39:51.275
Sam, I found Chris!
You can't get through this way!
Go around!

39:55.482 --> 39:59.612
[ Sam ]
I can't see. [ Coughing ]
I can't see anything.

39:59.686 --> 40:03.452
- I'm over here. Follow my voice.
- Keep talkin'.

40:03.523 --> 40:07.118
<i>I'm right here.</i>
<i>Keep comin'straight.</i>

40:07.193 --> 40:10.219
I can't see you.
I'm right over here.

40:11.965 --> 40:13.956
[ Coughing ]

40:15.735 --> 40:17.726
Al.

40:18.772 --> 40:21.935
Get outta the way! Get out of the way!

40:24.110 --> 40:26.806
His leg is pinned. Hurry up, Sam!

40:30.150 --> 40:32.880
<i>Hurry, Sam. Come on!</i>
<i>You gotta hurry up!</i>

40:38.458 --> 40:41.655
<i>You got him.</i>
<i>Now, pull him outta there!</i>

40:44.330 --> 40:48.596
<i>Come on, Sam.</i>
Al! Lead us outta here.
We're dyin' in here!

40:48.668 --> 40:51.694
This way, Sam! This way!

40:51.771 --> 40:55.172
Come on! You can do it!
[ Continues Coughing ]
We're comin'.

41:00.046 --> 41:02.412
[ Sirens Wailing ]

41:16.062 --> 41:19.190
Thank God you showed up.
I can't believe it. I want you to-- Oh!

41:19.265 --> 41:21.825
What the hell was that for?

41:25.572 --> 41:27.802
[ Coughing ]
Check his leg.

41:29.008 --> 41:31.806
<i>I think it's broken.</i>

41:31.878 --> 41:34.813
[ Coughing ]

41:38.418 --> 41:40.545
Looks like I got my stunt card,
huh, Dad?

41:51.164 --> 41:53.655
<i>[ Engine Revs, Siren Chirps ]</i>
Oh, look!

41:53.733 --> 41:58.636
You were exposed to all that heat,
but your mood ring's bright blue.

41:58.705 --> 42:00.866
You know what that means?

42:02.075 --> 42:04.407
I guess I'm in a good mood.

42:04.477 --> 42:08.914
<i>[ Father ] Get it! Get it! Ohh!</i>
<i>[ Chris ]</i>
<i>Get it in to the</i>-- <i>Get it, get it! Ohh!</i>

42:08.982 --> 42:12.247
Come on. You gotta get
those offensive boards.

42:12.318 --> 42:15.082
<i>[ Man On TV]</i>
<i>Great defensive move there. 1 02-79.</i>
<i>Just listen to the hand that they're getting.</i>

42:15.155 --> 42:18.420
Doesn't look good.
Does not look good, Dad.

42:18.491 --> 42:20.823
My pocket's gettin' full already.
Another beer?
You bet.

42:20.894 --> 42:24.057
...great defensive play.
[ Continues, Indistinct ]

42:24.130 --> 42:28.863
<i>[ Chris ] Did you see that? He missed another</i>
<i>one! Why do they keep passin'it to this guy?</i>
<i>[ Father ] Another one.</i>

42:28.935 --> 42:31.096
<i>Come on! Get it in the key!</i>
<i>Come on!</i>

42:31.171 --> 42:33.264
<i>[ TV]</i>
<i>He starts to drive, plays it off to Gibbons,</i>
<i>and he scores!</i>

42:34.774 --> 42:37.572
Oh! Al.

42:37.644 --> 42:40.272
Hi, Sam. How's it goin', pal?

42:40.346 --> 42:43.338
You tell me.
Why haven't I leaped?
<i>[ Chris ] Get it!</i>

42:43.416 --> 42:46.874
Well, Ziggy's workin' on that.
What's your rush?
<i>[ Chris, Father Shouting At TV]</i>

42:46.953 --> 42:50.013
Things seem to be lookin' up here.

42:50.089 --> 42:52.557
<i>[ Chris ]</i>
<i>Come on, come on!</i>
Oh, I-I don't know.

42:52.625 --> 42:56.186
I just, um--just feel
a little homesick, that's all.

42:56.262 --> 42:59.129
You know, sometimes I can't
help but think about--

42:59.199 --> 43:02.635
Well, you know I hope that
maybe I'll leap all the way back.

43:04.304 --> 43:06.363
Uh, forward, you mean.

43:06.439 --> 43:08.873
Yeah, well,
I don't even remember...

43:08.942 --> 43:12.708
where I lived, or, you know,
who my friends were
or if I had a dog or--

43:12.779 --> 43:14.940
No. You don't have a dog.

43:17.850 --> 43:20.876
Well, you know,just sometimes
you kind of feel alone, that's all.

43:20.954 --> 43:23.286
What do you mean, you're alone?

43:23.356 --> 43:27.452
I mean, it's not much,
but you got me.

43:29.462 --> 43:31.453
Uh, Sam--

43:32.465 --> 43:35.400
Sam, uh, I--
I shouldn't do this, but...

43:35.468 --> 43:37.436
here.

43:42.542 --> 43:44.908
It's Tom and me.

43:50.350 --> 43:52.409
Oh. I'm sorry, uh--

43:56.389 --> 43:59.017
I promise I'll save this for you.

44:01.461 --> 44:03.452
Thanks, Al.

44:05.898 --> 44:08.526
Come on.
Don't you want to watch the game?

44:16.109 --> 44:18.771
Jump shot!

44:18.845 --> 44:21.109
[ Men Groan ]

44:21.180 --> 44:23.171
- What happened?
- It's over.

44:23.249 --> 44:26.218
This thing is drivin' me nuts.
You'll get it off soon enough.

44:28.288 --> 44:30.313
And then what?

44:30.390 --> 44:33.826
He's got his card.
He'll come to work for us.

44:33.893 --> 44:36.191
What about his music?

44:36.262 --> 44:39.356
He's real good, Mr. Stone.
Real good.

44:41.401 --> 44:44.336
Well, yeah, I guess he's okay
for a stuntman.

44:44.404 --> 44:49.307
<i>Uh! Look, no offense, Chris, but...</i>

44:49.375 --> 44:54.244
- he shouldn't be a stuntman any more than--
-<i>[ Man ] We now switch</i>
<i>to a live broadcast of the president</i>--

44:54.314 --> 44:58.910
Heh! Gerald Ford.
Look, Chris's future is in his music.

44:58.985 --> 45:02.512
- Now you know the future.
-<i>[ Al ] Sam.</i>

45:02.588 --> 45:05.318
<i>I</i>--<i>Sam, I remember this.</i>

45:05.391 --> 45:09.555
- <i>He trips at the bottom of the stairs.</i>
- [ Woman ]
...in good spirits after their flight,

45:09.629 --> 45:12.689
waving to the crowd
of some 600 spectators.
Uh, yeah.

45:12.765 --> 45:15.427
Dad, I do know the future.

45:15.501 --> 45:19.062
- Ford's gonna trip down those stairs.
- No, no. Not again.

45:19.138 --> 45:24.701
- No way you know what he's gonna do.
This is live.
- I'll bet you Chris's future I do.

45:24.777 --> 45:27.837
- [ Men, Together] What?
- That's brilliant, Sam, brilliant.

45:27.914 --> 45:33.580
I say that Ford's gonna trip down these stairs.
And if I'm right, you get behind Chris
becoming a musician.

45:35.488 --> 45:38.457
- And if you're wrong?
- I get behind him becoming a stuntman.

45:38.524 --> 45:42.756
- Wait a minute. This is my future we're--
- Relax. Trust me. I know what I'm doin'.

45:43.863 --> 45:46.764
You're on, bud.

45:49.969 --> 45:52.938
[ Whispers ]
You sure this is where he trips?

45:53.005 --> 45:56.202
Ehh, pretty sure.

45:56.275 --> 45:59.506
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Thank you, Linda. You think we should</i>
<i>include this unofficial information?</i>

45:59.579 --> 46:02.241
- [ Linda ] Well-- Oh,just a minute.
They're coming down the stairs now...
- [ Pensive Humming ]

46:02.315 --> 46:04.545
to great applause
from the spectators, and--

46:04.617 --> 46:07.313
- Oop!
- [ All Laughing ]

46:08.721 --> 46:11.554
What a memory, huh?
What a memory!

46:11.624 --> 46:16.994
<i>[ Linda ] It looks like he'll be okay.</i>
<i>[ Man ] Uh, Linda, do you have visual</i>
<i>of the president at this time?</i>

46:37.583 --> 46:41.610
[ Thinking ]
Oh, my God. I'm Popeye!

46:53.099 --> 46:58.059
(music) Summer nights
fallin' around my shoulder (music)

46:59.739 --> 47:05.371
(music) The desert wind
blowin' across my mind (music)

47:07.146 --> 47:12.516
(music) Hold me tight out on the borderline (music)

47:13.519 --> 47:17.046
(music) It's a long way there
down a one-way trail (music)

47:17.123 --> 47:20.957
(music) To the love that I left behind (music)

47:21.961 --> 47:25.988
(music) Out of sight
Can't see past you and me (music)

47:26.065 --> 47:28.465
(music) I'm haunted like a wanted man (music)

47:28.534 --> 47:32.971
(music) Out of time
Too late, my mistake (music)

47:33.039 --> 47:36.008
(music) But you gotta understand (music)

47:36.075 --> 47:40.774
(music) I've been dealin' with the pain
of lovin' you the best I can (music)

47:42.849 --> 47:48.014
(music) And I'm just another stranger
lookin' for the promised land (music)

